First time trying this place out, made a $75 order for the family one night . Ordered it online waited the estimated 17min and went in to get my food.  My order was not ready. There was at least 6 people in the kitchen and the place wasn't busy (based of people in the establishment. Obviously I can't see how many online orders they're dealing with) ended up being 25-30min.  Since it was a large order I decided to check my food... -one order of 12 wings only had 9 wings. -I was missing two sides (large and small fries) -three entire meals were missing as well.  That's probably around $25+ worth of food I was missing. That's a third of my entire order! Are you kidding me? I would have been screwed if I walked away right away.  I spent maybe over 45minutes from order time until I left. Way too long for wings and fries. The employee's customer service was great and thy apologized for the inconvenience, which makes them professional in the customer service aspect, but in the fast food management aspect they're weak.  In the end, the food wasn't even good. The "Hot" flavored wings were flavorless and not spicy. The chicken tenders were super salty. The fries with seasoning are good.  My biggest pet peeve was that they don't even label the orders! I made a 75$ order and I'm supposed to just guess what flavor is which?! When I asked them to please label it beacause I don't know which is which, the just said sorry we don't do that..  Would not recommend. Will not return. I'd rather make the extra trip to go to Buffalo Wild Wings in college park.
